These scripts can be used to create .deb packages for snark. The building is
done inside a docker container to ensure a consistent build environment and
allow building for different Ubuntu versions.

Build a docker image based on e.g. Ubuntu 20.04, that has all the necessary
tools/libraries installed. Note, you need to specify a comma.deb that you
have already built using the scripts in comma.

> ./snark-package-docker-build 20.04 comma-1.2.3-ubuntu-20.04.deb 

You can optionally provide a path to a Vimba SDK .tgz file. If this is 
provided, the final package will include vimba support.

> ./snark-package-docker-build 20.04 comma-1.2.3-ubuntu-20.04.deb --vimba=Vimba_v4.2_Linux.tgz

Build deb package (e.g. snark version 1.2.3 for Ubuntu 20.04):
> ./snark-package-docker-run 20.04 1.2.3

If your snark reposity is not in ~/src/snark, but e.g. in ~/my/src/snark, run
(you also need to specify snark directory if you run as sudo, since default
location is ~):
> ./snark-package-docker-run 20.04 1.2.3 ~/my/src/snark

Debian package will be built in your current directory

Test that package is ok, e.g:
> ./snark-package-docker-test 20.04 snark-1.2.3-ubuntu-20.04.deb
